description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OAKDALE PARK PRIMARY CARE NETWORK&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Senior Clinical Pharmacist &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;30 - 37.5 hours per week&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Between £45,753 and £51,668&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;dependent on experience and qualifications&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Overdale Medical Practice and Park Medical Practice have formed a primary care network covering our practice population of 40,000. We are passionate about providing excellent care to our patients and are keen to further extend and develop our team of pharmacists to support this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will play a lead role in medicines management, optimising prescribing and improving quality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be an experienced pharmacist who will work to develop, manage and mentor the PCN clinical pharmacist team, currently comprising of three clinical pharmacists and a pharmacy technician.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will undertake structured medication reviews to proactively manage patients with complex polypharmacy, especially for older people and those in care homes. The post holder will implement prescribing decisions and request appropriate monitoring investigations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will work closely to support the wider practice teams to support safe and effective prescribing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About us&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Both of practices use SystmOne and have worked closely together across many years. We are passionate about providing high quality care and about developing our workforce. We cover a suburban population of 40,000 to the east of Derby City. Our PCN team comprises of social prescribers, a physio, three pharmacists and pharmacy technician and we will soon be recruiting a health and well-being coach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information please contact Heather Simpson at heather.simpson@nhs.net or 01332 821470 or Fiona Bolstridge at f.bolstridge@nhs.net on 01332 685116&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apply on NHS Jobs, closing date 30th November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date 8th December &lt;/p&gt;
